<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-818-978  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 818 978.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  Oct 30 1989 n441 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>80486 flunks math. (flaw in Intel Corp's microprocessor leads toerroneous calculations, product delays)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Halper, Mark.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Intel Corp announces the discovery of a defect in the 80486microprocessor will require a redesign of the device.andP;  The defectcauses the 486 to make inaccurate technical calculations.andP;  Ratherthan fix the problem with a software solution, as previous 486bugs were fixed, Intel is retooling its production lines toproduce a new version of the device.andP;  This redesignedmicroprocessor is expected to ship by the end of Nov 1989.andP;  IBMstops shipment of its 486-based Power Platform upgrade board andCompaq and other vendors planning 486-based products are puttingtheir systems on hold until a corrected version of the 80486 isavailable.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Intel Corp. (quality control).andO;Ticker:    INTC.andO;Product:   Intel 80486 (Microprocessor) (defects).andO;Topic:     MicroprocessorsDefectsProduct DelayQuality Control.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>